reviews.text: Very casual, rustic cha chan teng and Thai flavour, like an indoor dai pai dong. The Thai dishes we ordered tasted authentic and delicious, especially the yellow curry crab. The crab was full of roe. The sauce was rich in flavor and creamy. Satay were ok, flavourful but were deep fried. Prefer them grilled over charcoal. The veggies had pplenty of flavour and "wok hay". The pomelo salad was a first for me, a blend of pomelo chunks, fried shallots/ onions, green onion, cilantro.
Good
